{"type":"article","slug":"vir/content/69/10/2681","journal":"vir","canonical":"https://www.sgmjournals.org/vir/content/69/10/2681","meta":{"title":"Myristylation of Rotavirus Proteins","authors":["Clark, Billy","Desselberger, Ulrich"],"journalTitle":"Journal of General Virology","journalAbbrev":"","volume":"69","issue":"10","firstpage":"2681","lastpage":"","date":"10/01/1988","doi":"10.1099/0022-1317-69-10-2681","issn":[],"pmid":"2844975","mjid":"vir;69/10/2681","section":"","abstractUrl":"http://vir.sgmjournals.org/cgi/content/abstract/69/10/2681","fulltextUrl":"","pdfUrl":"http://vir.sgmjournals.org/cgi/reprint/69/10/2681.pdf","publicUrl":""},"abstractHtml":"<p>After labelling with [<sup>3</sup>H]myristic acid during replication the structural proteins VP6 and VP2 of purified rotavirus particles were found to be myristylated in an amide bond. [<sup>3</sup>H]Palmitic acid was converted to myristic acid before bonding to the viral proteins. Possible functions of rotavirus protein myristylation are discussed.</p>","bodyHtml":"","referencesHtml":"","affiliationsHtml":"","correspHtml":"","pdfPath":null,"summaryHtml":"","ccTier":"tier3-abstract","refdomains":0}